## Variants

### Basic modal (small, centered)
- **Title:** Short; centered; max two lines.
- **Body:** Multi-line descriptive text; centered.
- **Actions:** Secondary (left); Primary (right). No explicit close; backdrop click or secondary.

### Larger dialog
- **Header:** Title (left); optional checkbox; Close "X" (right).
- **Content:** Sticky banner; Date range; Body; Disclaimer at bottom.
- **Footer:** Secondary + primary buttons.

### Multi-panel modal
- **Header:** Title (left); Close "X" (right).
- **Left nav:** Section header (uppercase); Nav items with checkbox; Selected `--bg-brand-tertiary`.
- **Right content:** Same as larger dialog.
- **Footer:** Secondary + primary buttons.

---

## Sticky notification (inside modal)

| Element | Token |
|---------|-------|
| Teal (info) | `--bg-brand-tertiary` |
| Green (success) | `--bg-success-tertiary` |
| Yellow (warning) | `--bg-warning-tertiary` |
| Red (error) | `--bg-danger-tertiary` |
| Dismiss | Transparent; `--text-base-secondary` |
| Label button | `--bg-brand-default`, `--bg-success-default`, `--bg-warning-default`, or `--bg-danger-default`; `--text-brand-on-brand` |

---

## Footer actions

| Type | Surface | Text |
|------|---------|------|
| Primary | `--bg-brand-default` | `--text-brand-on-brand` |
| Secondary | `--bg-base-tertiary` | `--text-base-default` |
| Text | Transparent | "Dismiss" style |

---

## Close affordance

- "X" icon; `--text-base-default`; focus ring; right-aligned in header.

---

## Implementation guidelines

- Use tokens from `design-system-tokens.mdc` only.
- Focus trap inside modal; close on Escape; return focus to trigger on close.
- `role="dialog"` `aria-modal="true"` `aria-labelledby`.
- Do not invent variants; implement only what exists in Figma node 128:10421.
